<div class="app-card-container">
	<div class="card">
		<h1>About Me</h1>

		<hr>

		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-md-5">
				<%= image_tag "profile.jpg", width: 200, alt: "Profile Image", class: 'profile-img' %>
				<div class="skills">
					<% @skills.each do |skill| %>
						<div class="skill">
							<h4><%= skill.title %></h4>
							  <div class="progress">
							  	<div 
							  		class="progress-bar progress-bar-stripped bg-warning"
							  		role="progressbar"
							  		aria-valuenow="<%= skill.percent_level %>"
							  		aria-valuemax="100"
							  		style="width: <%= skill.percent_level %>%"
							  		>
							  	</div>
							  </div>
						</div>
					<% end %>					  
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="col-md-7">
				<p>With 4 years of a computer science Honours degree under my belt, Web develpemnt has become a real passion of mine.
				When developing for a client, communication is treated as the number one priority. Iterative development is what makes
				the client truly happy with their finished product.</p>
				<p>Check out my Portfolio for a better idea of how I can hone my Design skills to catch the users eye and keep them interested in your product through your website.</p>

				<p>
					<button
					class="btn btn-primary"
					type="button"
					data-toggle="collapse"
					data-target="#jobHistory"
					aria-expanded="false"
					aria-controls="jobHistory"
					>
						Job History
					</button>

					<button
					class="btn btn-primary"
					type="button"
					data-toggle="collapse"
					data-target="#education"
					aria-expanded="false"
					aria-controls="education"
					>
						Education
					</button>
				</p>
				<p>
					<div class="collapse" id="jobHistory">
						<div class="card card-block">
							Bus Eireann
						</div>
						<div class="card card-block">
							ICEP Europe
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="collapse" id="education">
						<div class="card card-block">
							BSc (Hons) in Computing, National College of Ireland
						</div>
					</div>
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>






